RESOURCE.STRING: SAE J1939 Datalink Control Test
SAE J1939 Datalink Control Test

This test can be used to selectively block datalink control devices while troubleshooting performance issues. Blocking a datalink device removes the restriction enforced by the device on engine speed, power, and torque.
Test Stopped. All the datalink devices will be set to normal default state as per the calibration.

Changes made to the datalink device state are still active and shall be reset to normal default setting after the keyswitch is cycled. You can also use the back or cancel controls to reset the datalink device.
Warning
All the datalink devices will be set to normal default state as per the calibration. Press OK to continue or Cancel to return to the test
Stop Test
. Press the Block All button and then press the Send to ECM button to block all the datalink devices.

Initial Conditions
1. Engine stopped
Steps
1. Select Start
2. Select an operation from below
A. Block Individual Data Link Device
i. Select the datalink device(s)
ii. Press the Send to ECM button
B. Block All Data Link Devices
i. Press the Block All button
ii. Press the Send to ECM button
C. Selectively Unblock Previously Blocked Device(s)
i. Undo Selection(s)
ii. Press the Send to ECM button
D. Unblock All Previously Blocked Device(s)
i. Press the Unblock All button
ii. Press the Send to ECM button
Additional Information
1. The datalink devices will be set to the default state if the key switch is cycled
2. A maximum of 4 devices can be blocked by individual selection
